{{Infobox cycling race report | name = 1935 Giro di Lombardia | date = October 20, 1935 | stages = 1 | distance = 238 | unit = km | first = [[Enrico Mollo]] | first_nat = ITA | second = [[Aldo Bini]] | second_nat = ITA | third = [[Gino Bartali]] | third_nat = ITA | previous = [[1934 Giro di Lombardia|1934]] | next = [[1936 Giro di Lombardia|1936]] }} The '''1935 Giro di Lombardia''' was the 31st edition of the race. It was held on October 20, 1935, with contestants riding a total route of 238&nbsp;km. It was won by the Italian [[Enrico Mollo]], reached the finish line with the time of 7h22 ' 16 "at an average of 32.288 km/h, preceding the countrymen [[Aldo Bini]] and [[Gino Bartali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bikeraceinfo.com/classics/Tour%20of%20Lombardy/1935-giro-di-lombardia.html|title=1935 Giro di Lombardia results (Tour of Lombardy)|work=BikeRaceInfo|accessdate=5 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.net/cla_lombardie/lombardie1935.php|title=31ème Giro di Lombardia 1935|work=Memoire du cyclisme|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040126154210/http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.net/cla_lombardie/lombardie1935.php|archivedate=26 January 2004}}</ref>
64 cyclists took off from Milan and 32 of them completed the race.
==Development== Mollo won this edition of the Giro of Lombardy culminating a solo escape originated in the first ascent of the day-mount Guello (km. 40). Bartali passed very close to him by the top but decided to wait for his companions thinking about the Italian championship, which was also decided in this test. This circumstance favored Mollo which by Grantola had more than eight minutes. A sufficient advantage to win the competition despite suffering in the last ascent to Brinzio.<ref>[http://hemeroteca.mundodeportivo.com/preview/1935/10/21/pagina-2/629882/pdf.html Noticia en Mundo Deportivo]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.les-sports.info/cyclisme-sur-route-tour-de-lombardie-resultats-1935-epr10564.html|title=Tour de Lombardie 1935|work=LesSports.info|accessdate=4 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=24&y=1935|title=1935 Il Lombardia|work=First Cycling|accessdate=4 January 2018}}</ref>
