The '''Chapel of Our Lady of the Snows'''<ref>[http://soldadosdigital.com/sitio/nota.asp?id=2269 Soldadosdigital.com]</ref> ({{lang-es|Capilla de Nuestra Señora de las Nieves}})<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nuestromar.org/noticias/categorias/05-08-15/conoce-capillas-cat-licas-ant-rtida|title=Conoce las capillas católicas de la Antártida, NUESTROMAR|website=www.nuestromar.org|access-date=2016-04-06}}</ref> is the name given to a temple excavated in a cave in the ice near the [[Belgrano II Base|Belgrano II base]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.messynessychic.com/2014/03/19/seven-churches-antarctica/|title=The Seven Churches of Antarctica|website=Messy Nessy Chic|access-date=2016-04-06}}</ref> in the territory it claims as part of [[Argentine Antarctica]]. It is one of [[List of Antarctic churches|eight churches on Antarctica]].
This church in a cave with walls made of ice is the most southern place of worship of any religion in the world. It is a permanent Catholic church for the whole year of Argentina base and scientific research station founded in 1955 on [[Coats Land]].
