'''European Imaging and Sound Association''' is a collaboration between different [[multimedia]] magazines, that offer tests of [[camera]]s, [[videocamera]]s, audio equipment, [[mobile phone]]s, etc. The organization was established in 1982. The current president of EISA is [[Paul Miller]]{{dn|date=November 2018}}.

In 2018 the organisation was renamed as the '''Expert Imaging and Sound Association''' to reflect new members from outside the European area, including Australian magazines '''Sound+Image''' and '''Australian Hi-Fi''', and US magazines '''Stereophile''' and '''Sound and Vision'''.

