{{Politics of the European Union}} The '''Committee on Foreign Affairs''' (AFET, after the French name "Affaires étrangères"), previously called '''Political Affairs''', is a [[committee]] of the [[European Parliament]]. Composed of 75 members and 74 substitutes, it has two subcommittees: the [[Subcommittee on Human Rights]] (DROI) and the [[Subcommittee on Security and Defence]] (SEDE).
Foreign affairs is not an area that Parliament has much power over, yet attracts a high proportion of the more well-known and influential MEPs given the prestige of the area{{Citation needed|date=October 2009}}.
==Members== For an up-to-date list of members, see: [http://www.europarl.europa.eu/committees/en/afet/members.html the European Parliament website: AFET members]
