The '''Flag of the City of [[Madrid]]''' represents the city's [[Coat of arms of Madrid|coat of arms]] centred on a [[crimson]] field.<ref>[http://www.munimadrid.es/portal/site/munimadrid/menuitem.8522c2ac1498b7f5b1e77112b95286a0/?vgnextoid=739d9d2e3fd4f010VgnVCM1000009b25680aRCRD&vgnextchannel=00dfb351fd18d010VgnVCM1000009b25680aRCRD&idSubPage=3 Ordinance ANM 1988\2 of the Madrid Council]</ref> The flag is made either in the proportions 3:5 or 2:3, and in shades of crimson corresponding to [[Pantone]] 207 or 208.

The significance of the bear leaning against a [[Arbutus unedo|madroño]], or strawberry tree, is unknown however, the tree is native to Madrid. One known theory is that bear and tree represent a farming rights dispute between the clergy and citizens. The seven stars supposedly represent the seven stars in the [[Big Dipper|Starry Plough]] constellation closest to the [[Ursa Major]] (Great Bear) Constellation. These stars symbolise the North and therefore, since North is the direction on which all others are based, the stars represent Madrid as the seat of government for Spain.<ref>[http://www.ctspanish.com/communities/madrid/madrid.htm Madrid the Capital of Spain]</ref>

